import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zip_count = data.groupby('state')['zip_code'].count()
    ax = zip_count.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 6), color='c')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Zip Codes'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by county and count the number of zip codes
    zip_count = data.groupby('county')['zip_code'].count().sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    # Create a bar chart
    ax = zip_count.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(20, 10), color='blue', legend=True)
    
    # Set title and labels
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across counties?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('County')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    
    # Rotate x-axis labels for better readability
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], c=data['state'].cat.codes, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude coordinates?', wrap=True)
    plt.colorbar().set_label('State')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts()
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white').generate_from_frequencies(city_counts)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.title("What is the most common city associated with a zip code?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['zip_code'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip code frequencies?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Zip Code')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.axvline(data['zip_code'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['zip_code'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
